  tips: [
    {
      label: "Don't miss the Mashantucket Pequot Museum",
      body: "This is the under-the-radar attraction most visitors skip. The Museum and Research Center sits on the same complex as the casino and is one of the largest Native American museums in the country. Permanent exhibits cover 18,000 years of regional Indigenous history, the Pequot War, and the Tribe's modern revitalization. There's also a 185-foot observation tower with panoramic views. Allow 2-3 hours. Admission is reasonable (around $20 adult, less for kids and seniors) and entirely separate from anything happening at the casino.",
